<h6><Center>PERSONAL GUARANTY</center></h6>
<ol>
<li><p>For value received and in consideration of and in order to induce <?PHP echo $property['propertyLLC'] ?>,  (the "Landlord") to enter into that certain Lease Agreement dated the <?php echo date("jS \of F, Y"); ?>, between Landlord and  	<?php echo $tenantName;?>				(the "Tenant"), for space at <?PHP echo $property['propertyName'] ?> (the "Lease") and other good and valuable considerations, the undersigned (hereinafter sometimes called the "Guarantor"), acting as principal and not as surety, absolutely, unconditionally, irrevocably, independent of Tenantâ€™s obligations under the Lease, for himself and his legal representatives, successors, and assigns, guarantees to Landlord and to its legal representatives, successors, and assigns, the prompt and full performance and observance by Tenant and by its legal representatives, successors, and assigns, of all of the covenants, terms, provisions, conditions, and agreements required to be performed by Tenant under the Lease, whether prior to, during the Term of, or after the termination of the Term of the Lease.</li>

<li><p>The capitalized terms used in this Guaranty shall have the same definitions as such capitalized terms have in the Lease unless the context clearly indicates a contrary intent.</li>

