	<li><p>Guarantor irrevocably consents that any legal action or proceeding arising out of or in any way connected with this Guaranty may be instituted or brought by Landlord or its agents in any court (federal or state) located in Pinellas County, Florida, and irrevocably submits to the jurisdiction of such court in any such legal action or proceeding.
	<li><p>Landlord has entered into the Lease on the condition that Guarantor shall maintain a minimum net worth ("Minimum Net Worth"), which is not less than the Guarantor's net worth as set forth in the financial statements submitted by Guarantor to Landlord prior to the making of the Lease, or if no financial statements were submitted by Guarantor to Landlord, then below a level deemed acceptable by Landlord in its sole and absolute discretion.  Consequently, within fifteen (15) days after Landlord's request, Guarantor will furnish to Landlord, Guarantor's most recent financial statements, IRS tax returns and W-2 forms for the immediately preceding 2 calendar years, pay stubs for the immediately preceding 12 pay periods, all bank account (checking, savings, money-market and the like) statements for the immediately preceding 24 months in which Guarantor was named on the account, credit card statements for the preceding 24 months in which Guarantor was authorized to sign, credit applications for the preceding 24 months, credit reports obtained from any credit reporting agencies for the preceding 24 months, and any other financial records which would be discoverable in aid of execution in the State of Florida.  Guarantor agrees that Landlord and its agents and attorneys have the right to obtain Guarantorâ€™s personal credit reports and financial statements from Guarantor, Guarantor's creditors, and other third parties in connection with the extension of credit pursuant to this Guaranty, subsequently in connection with its interest in determining Guarantor's financial condition at any time during the term of this Guaranty, and after the term of this Guaranty until all obligations under this Guaranty are fully discharged. Any of Landlord's requests for documents and information as set forth herein may be made at any time during and after the Term of the Lease, during and after the term of this Guaranty, including but not limited to periods when enforcement and collection litigation in connection with the Lease or this Guaranty is taking place, and in such litigation, such records shall be deemed discoverable without objection from Guarantor and all objections thereto shall be deemed and are hereby waived.  During such periods, Guarantor will discuss its financial statements with Landlord and will give Landlord access to Guarantor's books and records in order to enable Landlord to verify the financial statements and other financial information.  The failure of Guarantor to strictly comply with the foregoing the requirements of this paragraph, time being of the essence, shall constitute a material default of this Guaranty. Landlord will not disclose any aspect of Guarantor's financial statements that Guarantor designates to Landlord as confidential except (a) to Landlord's consultants, lenders or prospective purchasers of the Project, (b) in litigation between Landlord and Tenant, and (c) if required by court order.  Landlord has the right to report to others its credit experience.  Landlord has the right to contact Guarantorâ€™s major creditors to discuss the status of the Lease and this Guaranty, the credit and payment history of Guarantor, Guarantor's financial condition, and any other relevant matters. Upon request, Landlord will inform Guarantor of the name and address of each consumer reporting agency from which a credit report is obtained.
	<li><p>Should Guarantor's net worth fall below the Minimum Net Worth level as a result of a transfer of Guarantor's assets or an increase in Guarantor's liabilities and not as a result of fluctuations in the market value of Guarantor's assets, such event shall constitute a default under this Guaranty and under the Lease.  In such event, Landlord may declare all forms of Rent due under the Lease for the remainder of the Term of the Lease to be forthwith due and payable notwithstanding any stay, injunction, or other prohibition preventing such declaration as against Tenant and, in the event of any such declaration by Landlord, such obligations (whether or not due and payable by Tenant) shall forthwith become due and payable by Guarantor under this Guaranty.
